1 employee of a municipality who alleges that disciplinary action has been
2 taken against such officer or employee in violation of this section may
3 bring an action in a court of competent jurisdiction within 90 days after the
4 occurrence of the alleged violation seeking damages and any other
5 equitable relief the court deems necessary. The court may award the
6 prevailing party in the action all or a portion of the costs of the action,
7 including reasonable attorney fees and witness fees.
8 (2) In any municipality that creates an administrative process to
9 adjudicate disciplinary actions against employees of the municipality,
10 any officer or employee of the municipality who is eligible to appeal
11 disciplinary actions to such adjudicative body may appeal to such body
12 whenever such officer or employee alleges that disciplinary action was
13 taken against such officer or employee in violation of this act. The
14 appeal shall be filed within 90 days after the alleged disciplinary action.
15 If such body finds that the disciplinary action taken was unreasonable,
16 such body shall modify or reverse the auditing agency's{ municipality's}
17 action and order such relief for the employee as such body considers
18 appropriate. Any party may appeal a decision of such governing body
19 under the Kansas judicial review act, K.S.A. 77-601 et seq., and
20 amendments thereto.
21 (f) Each municipality shall prominently post a copy of this act in
22 locations where it can reasonably be expected to come to the attention of
23 all employees of such municipality.
24 (g) Nothing in this act shall be construed to negate or supersede
25 any provision of law providing protection against liability to a legislator
26 for any act or failure to act, impose any liability against a legislator for
27 any act or failure to act or create a duty upon a legislator to take any
28 action based on any information that may be shared with a legislator by
29 a municipal employee or any other person.
30 Sec. 2. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
31 publication in the statute book.

